Criminals have infiltrated the boda boda business and are using it as a ruse to commit crimes, a county commissioner has said.
 The trend has raised concern within security agents, as the thugs use the trade to escape arrests. Kassim Farrah, has issued a stern warning to those in the business of perpetrating crime and masquerading as taxi operators. 
